Package frc.robot

Class SwerveDriveModuleControl

java.lang.Object
frc.robot.SwerveDriveModuleControl
public class SwerveDriveModuleControl extends Object
Class to hold a module's configuration information, read module sensors, calculate module control logic and output to module actuators.
File: SwerveDriveModuleControl.java

Referenceable items: (classes)
SwerveDriveModuleControl

Depends on:
rev SparkMax - motor controller library ctre CanCoder - canConder encoder library.
Operating system specifics:
None - transportable

    • ExecuteLogic

      public void ExecuteLogic(edu.wpi.first.math.kinematics.SwerveModuleState desiredModuleState, double timeValue)
      Calculate the desired motor outputs for spin and drive motors based on the desired state and already read sensor data. This does not output to motor controllers, allowing this to be used either for real robots or simulated robots. The appropriate output routine would need to be called.
      Parameters:
      desiredModuleState - - SwerveModuleState - The desired state of this module
      timeValue - - double - system elapsed time in seconds.
